---
description: Section-divider comment policy — allowed between methods, forbidden inside functions.
globs: "**/*.py"
---

Section-divider comments like `# ====== Text Encoding ======` are **allowed between methods/functions** at class or module scope. They improve navigation in large adapter/trainer files.

Section-divider comments are **forbidden inside function bodies**. Use plain numbered comments instead.

Allowed (between methods):
```python
    # ============================== Text Encoding ==============================

    def encode_prompt(self, ...):
        ...

    # ============================== Decoding ==============================

    def decode_latents(self, ...):
        ...
```

Forbidden (inside a function):
```python
def inference(self, ...):
    # ========== 0. Validate inputs ==========   # BAD
    ...
    # ========== 1. Encode prompts ==========     # BAD
```

Use instead:
```python
def inference(self, ...):
    # 0. Validate inputs
    ...
    # 1. Encode prompts
```
